# GitHub API Token (Optional but HIGHLY RECOMMENDED for production)
# 
# Rate Limits:
#   - Without token: 60 requests/hour (very limited)
#   - With token: 5,000 requests/hour (production ready)
#
# How to get a token:
#   1. Go to: https://github.com/settings/tokens
#   2. Click "Generate new token" (classic)
#   3. Give it a name (e.g., "github-analytics")
#   4. Select scope: "public_repo" (read-only)
#   5. Copy the token and paste below
#
# For Vercel Deployment:
#   1. Create the token as above
#   2. Go to Vercel Project Settings
#   3. Navigate to Environment Variables
#   4. Add: GITHUB_TOKEN = <your-token>
#   5. Apply to all environments (Production, Preview, Development)
#

GITHUB_TOKEN=your_github_personal_access_token_here
